article.headline: Arizona 100, Bryant 60
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. -- Brendan Lavender sank 6 of 8 3-point shots -- 5 of 6 in the second half -- en route to a career-high 18 points, and Arizona routed Bryant 100-60 Thursday night in its final tuneup for Pac-12 play. Jesse Perry added 16 points on 7 of 8 shooting and grabbed 10 rebounds for the Wildcats (9-4). Solomon Hill scored 13 points and Kevin Parrom and Kyle Fogg had 11 apiece for Arizona, which is off until Dec. 31, when it begins conference play with a home game against Arizona State. Corey Maynard scored 22 points and Alex Francis 17 for the Bulldogs (1-11). Four of Lavender's 3-pointers came in a 32-5 second-half burst that put Arizona up 82-39 with just under nine minutes to play.
